==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|becomen}}, {{m|enm|bicumen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|becuman|t=to come (to), approach, arrive, enter, meet with, fall in with; happen, befall; befit}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*bikwemaną||to come around, come about, come across, come by}}, equivalent to {{prefix|en|be|t1=about, around|come}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|becum||to come, arrive, reach a destination}}, {{cog|frr|bekommen}}, {{m|frr|bykommen||to come by, obtain, receive}}, {{cog|fy|bikomme||to come by, obtain, receive}}, {{cog|nl|bekomen||to come by, obtain, receive}}, {{cog|de|bekommen||to get, receive, obtain}}, {{cog|sv|bekomma||to receive, concern}}, {{cog|got|𐌱𐌹𐌵𐌹𐌼𐌰𐌽||to come upon one, befall}}. Sense of "befit, suit" due to influence from {{ncog|enm|cweme}}, {{m|enm|icweme}}, see {{m|en|queem}}.

